Enable system wide debugging features

Features

sysrq
sysrq key is a 'magical' key combo you can hit which the kernel will respond to
regardless of whatever else it is doing, unless it is completely locked up.
It is enabled by distro feature "systemdebug" for systemd and kernel feature
features/sysrq. For more details please refer to
https://github.com/torvalds/linux/blob/master/Documentation/admin-guide/sysrq.rst
